# GW rules downloads (Warhammer Community)

**RED LINE:** See `.cursor/rules/eleventh_edition_only.mdc` - old editions and superseded layouts must never reach Firestore or the API.

Use the **official downloads search API**, not HTML scraping or headless browsers.

## Discovery

```http
POST https://www.warhammer-community.com/api/search/downloads/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "index": "downloads_v2",
  "searchTerm": "",
  "gameSystem": "warhammer-40000",
  "language": "english"
}
```

Response `hits[]` include `title`, `download_categories[]`, and `id.file` (PDF filename).
Asset URL: `https://assets.warhammer-community.com/{id.file}`

Human index page (reference only): https://www.warhammer-community.com/en-gb/downloads/warhammer-40000/

## Politeness (required)

- **Sequential downloads only** - no parallel requests
- **Default 5s delay** between PDF fetches (`--delay` to increase if needed)
- **Identifying User-Agent**: `roboto-guilliman/0.1 (+https://github.com/Tyberium/roboto-guilliman; rules-ingest-tool)`
- **Backoff** on HTTP 429/503 (exponential, cap 120s)
- **Skip unchanged** files via SHA256 manifest at `data/rules/manifest.json`
- **Never run bulk download in CI** unless explicitly requested - manual or scheduled local/job only

## Storage and copyright

- Save PDFs under `data/rules/{parser_profile}/` (gitignored). Profiles match chunking strategy:
  `core_rules`, `updates_and_faq`, `reference`, `faction_packs`, `event_companions`, `miscellaneous`, `excluded`
- `excluded/` holds Sep 2024 layout core rules and quick start - **never ingested** (see `eleventh_edition_only.mdc`)
- Mapping lives in `roboto_guilliman/ingestion/source_registry.py`
- Legacy flat layout: `poetry run download-rules --migrate-legacy`
- Re-file PDFs after mapping changes: `poetry run download-rules --reconcile`
- **Never commit** PDFs or rules text to the repo
- Ingest chunks go to **private** Firestore only; do not expose GW content in docs, demos, or logs

## CLI

```bash
poetry run download-rules              # full sync, 5s between files
poetry run download-rules --dry-run    # list only
poetry run download-rules --force      # re-download all
```

After download, inspect chunks with `poetry run preview-chunks` before ingest.
